==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Secern
<hw>Se*cern"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Secerned</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Secerning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>secernere</ets>. See <er>Secrete</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
separate; to distinguish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Averroes <qex>secerns</qex> a sense of titillation, and a sense of
hunger and thirst.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>To secrete; <as>as, mucus
<ex>secerned</ex> in the nose</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Arbuthnot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Secernent</ent>⟦br⟧
